-- South Africa's Eskom to `Urgently' Start Program to Close Its Funding Gap
-- B y   N i c k y   S m i t h
-- 2010-11-04T07:15:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-04/south-africa-s-eskom-to-urgently-start-program-to-close-its-funding-gap.html
South Africa’s power utility Eskom
will urgently start a program to close its funding gap over the
next two to three years, Brain Dames, the chief executive
officer, said in Johannnesburg today.  The company will look “locally and globally” to find the
extra funds it needs, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
